[Introduction of vaccination to protect the high-risk groups is a priority intervention to reduce the burden of influenza. In individuals belonging to the high-risk groups, it is important to initiate treatment early in order to prevent influenza-associated complications and help reduce mortality. To prevent further transmission of the disease in the community, it is necessary to maintain respiratory and hand hygiene and stay at home during the illness. - Mod.UBA]

