[7] Miami, Florida USA
Date: 17 Jan 2020
Source: ABC 6 [edited]
https://abc6onyourside.com/news/local/miami-trace-local-school-district-closed-friday-due-to-flu-outbreak


The Miami Trace Local School District will be closed on Fri 17 Jan 2020 due to a flu outbreak.

The school district said it is currently experiencing a high volume of influenza B cases throughout the district.

The district has been working with the Fayette County Health Department to monitor the situation, and as a result, the district will be closed Friday [17 Jan 2020]. As a precautionary measure, the entire district will be shut down until the start of school Tuesday [21 Jan 2020]. Closing schools will allow 4 days for facilities and buses to be disinfected.

All district activities and contests are also canceled this weekend, including youth programs.

[Byline: Jarrod Clay]

